  <name>Auqw</name>
  <summary>Native cross-platform music player</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Auqw is a native music player built with a Qt/QML shell and a durable Zig core, focused on local playback, queue control, online provider search, and provider-backed downloads.
    </p>
    <p>
      The first release keeps provider code isolated, avoids account login, and saves provider download streams without yt-dlp or transcoding.
    </p>
  </description>
